<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.1.11" />

<note type="curatorial">14 Davis Coll <hi rend="caps">N Y</hi> Pub Lib</note>
<note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">STATE HISTORICAL SOCIETY OF MISSOURI</hi></note>
<fw type="curatorial">11</fw>

<opener>
<hi rend="caps">RHD-C117</hi>

<dateline>July 17,1906.</dateline>
<address>
<addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt, Esq.,</addrLine>

<addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska.</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Just a plain, ordinary white man's farewell before I dig for Maine, whither I drift the day after tomorrow.</p>

<p>Don't ever get the impression that anything you leave unsaid in your letters is for that reason unseen. You answer a great many more questions than I ask every time you write to me.</p>

<p>No matter where you are, my friend, you will find the lice of civilization crawling around annoying you. A restless spirit never really gets among his own people, because his own people are equally restless, hustling along the Riviera of life, seldom stopping or looking backward.</p>

<p>I await with pleasure the coming of Streamer.</p>

<p>Keep your pipe lit, and smoke a tobacco that does not burn the tongue. This insures long life and peace of mind in a turbulent world, more or less afflicted with a gratitude that appears to have the spring halt.</p>
<closer>


<salute>Always sincerely,</salute>
</closer>
  
</div1>
